<dl id="n25186j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n25" href="#n25186j">N25 (VI.B.15)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n25all.htm#n25186j"> 186(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> recline at ease</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The &ldquo;cup of blessing&rdquo; was as much a part of the Passover rite, in the time of our Lord, as was the custom of &ldquo;<mark>reclining at ease</mark>&rdquo; to eat the unleavened bread. <small> Claude R. Conder, <a name="CRRM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CRRM"><cite title="source">The Rise of Man</cite></a> (1908) 323</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c14126l" href="c14all.htm#c14126l">VI.C.14:126(l)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
